    ]
  },
  {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do I choose the correct MCB rating?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Calculate load current (Watts ÷ 230V), apply a 1.25 safety margin, and round up to the next standard MCB rating: 6A, 10A, 16A, 20A, 25A, 32A, 40A, 50A, or 63A. For motor loads (AC, pump, fridge), use a Type C curve MCB. For lights and pure resistive loads, use Type B." }},
