      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the difference between a B curve and C curve MCB?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Type B MCBs have a magnetic trip threshold of 3–5× rated current and are used for resistive loads (lighting, heaters). Type C MCBs trip at 5–10× rated current and are designed for inductive/motor loads (ACs, pumps, refrigerators) that produce starting current surges." }},
